---
import "../../styles/global.css";
import Navbar from "../../components/Navbar.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <title>S.U.S.D.E.M — Underwater Monitoring System</title>
  </head>

  <body>
    <Navbar />

    <main class="project-page">
      <section class="project-hero">
        <img src="/projects/underwater.jpeg" alt="S.U.S.D.E.M Project" class="hero-img" />
        <div class="overlay">
          <h1>S.U.S.D.E.M — Underwater Monitoring System</h1>
          <p>Autonomous underwater platform for pH and turbidity monitoring to detect eutrophication early.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="project-content">
        <h2>Project Overview</h2>
        <p>
          The <strong>Submersible Underwater System for Detecting Eutrophication Monitoring (S.U.S.D.E.M)</strong> 
          was designed as a low-cost autonomous underwater vehicle for collecting and transmitting 
          real-time water quality data. It integrates sensors for <strong>pH</strong>, 
          <strong>turbidity</strong>, and <strong>temperature</strong>, controlled by dual 
          <strong>ESP32 microcontrollers</strong> communicating via <strong>I2C</strong>. 
          The structure combines <strong>PVC housing</strong> for waterproofing and 
          <strong>PLA supports</strong> for sensor mounts.
        </p>

        <h2>System Architecture</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Control Unit:</strong> Two ESP32 boards — one for motor control and another for sensor data.</li>
          <li><strong>Actuation System:</strong> Three DC motors for movement and immersion stability.</li>
          <li><strong>Sensor Suite:</strong> pH, turbidity, and TDS sensors connected via I2C.</li>
          <li><strong>Mechanical Design:</strong> Compact PLA–PVC body designed for durability and corrosion resistance.</li>
          <li><strong>Communication:</strong> Real-time serial link to surface for live visualization and analysis.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Design Highlights</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>3D printed <strong>PLA supports</strong> for modular assembly and sensor alignment.</li>
          <li><strong>Waterproof PVC housing</strong> with sealed cable glands for reliable underwater operation.</li>
          <li><strong>Three-motor system</strong> for precise horizontal and vertical motion control.</li>
          <li>Synchronized microcontrollers integrating <strong>sensor feedback</strong> and <strong>motor actuation</strong>.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Challenges & Solutions</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Waterproofing:</strong> Achieved with silicone seals and pressure-tested PVC enclosures.</li>
          <li><strong>Pressure Resistance:</strong> Structure validated up to 15 m depth operation.</li>
          <li><strong>Data Accuracy:</strong> Sensor calibration routines ensure precise readings.</li>
          <li><strong>Communication:</strong> Reliable I2C data synchronization between ESP32 modules.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Impact</h2>
        <p>
          S.U.S.D.E.M showcases how mechatronic systems can contribute to <strong>environmental monitoring</strong>. 
          By automating the collection of water-quality data, it enables researchers and authorities 
          to detect early signs of eutrophication and implement preventive conservation strategies.
        </p>

        <section class="back-link">
          <a href="/projects">← Back to Projects</a>
        </section>
      </section>
    </main>

    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>

<style>
.project-page {
  color: var(--color-text);
  line-height: 1.7;
}

.project-hero {
  position: relative;
  height: 60vh;
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center;
  align-items: center;
  overflow: hidden;
}

.hero-img {
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
  object-fit: cover;
  filter: brightness(55%);
}

.overlay {
  position: absolute;
  text-align: center;
  color: white;
  z-index: 2;
}

.overlay h1 {
  font-size: 2.5rem;
  font-family: var(--font-title);
  margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
}

.overlay p {
  font-size: 1.1rem;
}

.project-content {
  max-width: 900px;
  margin: 4rem auto;
  padding: 0 2rem;
}

.project-content h2 {
  color: var(--color-accent);
  margin-top: 2rem;
  margin-bottom: 0.8rem;
}

.project-content ul {
  margin-left: 1.5rem;
  list-style-type: square;
}

.back-link {
  text-align: center;
  margin-top: 3rem;
}

.back-link a {
  color: var(--color-accent);
  font-weight: 600;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  font-size: 0.9rem;
  letter-spacing: 1px;
  transition: color 0.3s ease, transform 0.3s ease;
  text-decoration: none;
}

.back-link a:hover {
  color: var(--color-deep);
  transform: translateX(-4px);
}
</style>
